{'id_' : 'eu|consecration_en_US_dedes|euMA|Kontakion|text', 'text' : 'Lord, Your Church appears to us * to be like heaven * full of light, and guides with light * all who believe in You, O Christ. * And we who stand in it cry to You: * Savior, establish forever this holy house.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|consecration_en_US_dedes|euMA|Oikos|text', 'text' : 'After the Logos had dwelt among us in the flesh, John, that Son-of-Thunder, wrote, "We beheld the glory, which the Son had from the Father, in grace and truth." To all of us, who received Him by faith, He gave power to become children of God. And now, born again, not of blood nor of the will of the flesh, but raised by the Holy Spirit, we have erected a house of prayer, and we say, "Savior, establish forever this holy house."'}
{'id_' : 'eu|consecration_en_US_dedes|euMA|Ode7C1H|ode', 'text' : 'Ode vii.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|consecration_en_US_dedes|euMA|Ode7C1H|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
