{'id_' : 'eu|consecration_en_US_dedes|euMA|Ode8C1H|text', 'text' : 'Daniel shut the lions' gaping mouths inside the den, of old, by stretching out his hands. * The Servants girt themselves with virtue; * and, as lovers of godliness, * they put out the mighty fire * in the furnace, and cried aloud, * singing, "Bless the Lord, all you works of the Lord."'}
